  "rawMarkdown" : "---\nsource: https:\/\/developer.apple.com\/documentation\/security\/seccsflags\ncrawled: 2025-12-14T07:09:33Z\n---\n\n# SecCSFlags\n\n**Structure**\n\nValues that can be used in the `flags` parameter to most code signing functions.\n\n## Declaration\n\n```swift\nstruct SecCSFlags\n```\n\n## Overview\n\nAll of the bits in the [doc:\/\/com.apple.security\/documentation\/Security\/SecCSFlags] enumeration are reserved by Apple. If you set any bits not defined here, the behavior is undefined.\n\n## Initializers\n\n- **init(rawValue:)**\n\n## Constants\n\n- **considerExpiration**: Consider expired certificates invalid.\n- **enforceRevocationChecks**\n- **checkTrustedAnchors**\n- **noNetworkAccess**\n- **reportProgress**\n- **quickCheck**\n\n## Type Properties\n\n- **applyEmbeddedPolicy**\n- **matchGuestRequirementInKernel**\n- **stripDisallowedXattrs**\n\n## Conforms To\n\n- BitwiseCopyable\n- Equatable\n- ExpressibleByArrayLiteral\n- OptionSet\n- RawRepresentable\n- Sendable\n- SendableMetatype\n- SetAlgebra\n\n",
